cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D pose estimation and 3D model retrieval from RGB images. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes a scalable and efficient approach for object recognition and retrieval, which can be useful in robotics applications. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses a CNN-based multi-view metric learning approach for matching learned image descriptors. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an approach for accurately representing the geometry of objects in the wild, which can be useful in AI applications such as autonomous driving. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with 3D models and rendering depth images.
